STACK OPERATIONS IN C:

In this program, the user is asked to input a line.
The characters in the line are put on a stack.  Then
the characters are read off of the stack and printed.
This causes the line to be printed in reverse order
on the screen.

The object of this program is not to reverse a line;
we already know how to do that.  The point is to
exercise the stack operations.

---
After you have executed the program and understand its
effects, you should change one of the lines in main.c
as follows:

   from: #define   MAXDATA   1000
     to: #define   MAXDATA   10

Recompile the program and run it again.
What happens when you enter a long line?

